 A US businessman sentenced yesterday to 20 years hard labor in Russia is
 waiting to hear if he will be pardoned. Edmund Pope denies spying charges.
 He has written to President Vladimir Putin to request his release. A
 Presidential Pardons Commission will meet tomorrow to consider the request.
 It's expected to recommend granting the pardon. BBC News for The World. I am
 Gregor Cragey.
